exceptions.tactic: exists (fun a => exists c, f' a = f c).
exceptions.exn: In environment A : Type f : A -> Ens E' : Ens P : A -> Prop H1 : EQ E' (sup (depprod A (fun a : A => P a)) (fun c : depprod A (fun a : A => P a) => match c with | @dep_i _ _ a _ => f a end)) A' : Type f' : A' -> Ens H0 : IN (sup A' f') E' The term "fun a : A' => exists c : A, f' a = f c" has type "A' -> Prop" while it is expected to have type "A".

original: intros E E' H. unfold Power in H. unfold IN in H. unfold INC. intros E'' H0. destruct E as [A f]. simpl in *. destruct H as [P H1]. simpl in H1. rewrite H1. destruct E'' as [A' f']. simpl. exists (fun a => exists c, f' a = f c). simpl. reflexivity.
